  "text": "In both of these cases (lignin-SiO2 8:1, wt./wt. and 8:2, wt./wt.) an increased crosslinking density can be observed as a result of interaction between lignin and silica particles. Lignin presents a high quantity of activated free ring positions, which may react with other compounds [CITATION_1] . The high reactivity of the hybrid fillers can be associated with a high crosslinking density. The presence of In both of these cases (lignin-SiO 2 8:1, wt./wt. and 8:2, wt./wt.) an increased crosslinking density can be observed as a result of interaction between lignin and silica particles. Lignin presents a high quantity of activated free ring positions, which may react with other compounds [CITATION_2] . The high reactivity of the hybrid fillers can be associated with a high crosslinking density. The presence of rigid functional groups can restrict the distance between nodes in the polymer network and thus increase the crosslinking density [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
